# diffusers structure & registration

No `.ai/` doc covers the single-file policy + import-registration footprint — this rule is genuine pack value.
For general style defer to `AGENTS.md` (= `.ai/AGENTS.md`) / `diffusers-style`. The registration gotcha is
also flagged in `.ai/models.md` gotcha #1.

## Single-file policy
- One self-contained file per component. **Copy an existing similar component; do not invent abstractions.**
  - Schedulers: `src/diffusers/schedulers/scheduling_<name>.py`
  - Pipelines: `src/diffusers/pipelines/<name>/pipeline_<name>.py`
  - Models: `src/diffusers/models/<subdir>/<name>.py` (`models/unets/`, `models/transformers/`, …)
- **Every new top-level component file** (a new scheduler / pipeline / model `.py`) starts with the standard
  HuggingFace Apache-2.0 header (copy it verbatim from the top of any current
  `src/diffusers/schedulers/scheduling_*.py`). `__init__.py` files and small `pipeline_output.py` dataclass
  files routinely omit it.

## Import registration is 4 lines across 2 files (easy to under-do)
A new scheduler `XxxScheduler` must be registered in **both** `__init__.py` files, each in two places:
```python
# 1) src/diffusers/schedulers/__init__.py
_import_structure["scheduling_xxx"] = ["XxxScheduler"]   # in the is_torch_available() branch
from .scheduling_xxx import XxxScheduler                  # in the TYPE_CHECKING block

# 2) src/diffusers/__init__.py  (top level — NOT picked up transitively)
_import_structure["schedulers"].extend([..., "XxxScheduler", ...])
from .schedulers import (..., XxxScheduler, ...)          # in the TYPE_CHECKING block
```
Use the lazy `_import_structure` + `_LazyModule` pattern. Insert each new entry in its **alphabetical
position** among the sibling `scheduling_*.py` entries (e.g. `scheduling_ddim_variant` sorts after
`scheduling_ddim_parallel`, before `scheduling_ddpm`) — `custom_init_isort` enforces sorted order, so a wrong
slot churns the diff. `src/diffusers/utils/dummy_pt_objects.py` is **auto-generated by `make fix-copies`** —
never hand-edit it, but expect it in your diff.
